data.value:
verse 1:
Hei hyvä haltija heilauta taikasauvaa
Tai noitaruhtinatar, hoida, vihreää ihmejuomaa
Ei kaniinia hatusta, ei enempää suolaa
Voisiko joku tämän kerran toiveeni toteuttaa

chorus:
Abrakadabra, tän täytyy toimia
Abrakadabra, ala rakastaa minua

verse 2:
Ne lepakonkynnet, ja liskonkeiton syön
Kuin nöyrä noviisi loitsuja luen tän yön
Näkyykö valoa kristallipallossa
Vai piinaanko ruumistani turhissa unelmissa

bridge:
Selasin Sudenpentujen käsikirjan ja Pikku Jättiläisen
Joo suutelen sammakon viimeisen katseesta yhden naisen

verse 1:
Hello good fairy wave a magic wand
Or witch princess, treat, green wonder potion
No rabbit in the hat, no more salt
Could someone make my wish come true for once?

chorus:
Abracadabra, this must work
Abracadabra, start loving me

verse 2:
I'll eat those bat claws and lizard soup
Like a humble novice I recite spells tonight
Can you see the light in the crystal ball
Or do I torture my body in vain dreams

bridge:
I looked through the Scout's Handbook and the information book for young people
Yeah, I'll kiss the last frog, for the look of one woman
Tornion Lappian muusikot - Abrakadabra (alkuperäinen esittäjä Mikko Kuustonen)

Miksasin koulutehtävänä ammattilaismuusikoiden Abrakadabra kappaletta ja ajattelin pystyväni samaan. Tuntui turhalta nauhoittaa sama kappale, joten tein oman, jossa on vielä löyhästi kuultavista ei-kopiosuojattuja ominaisuuksia Abrakadabrasta.

Verse 1:
Hello, good fairy waving her wand,
or witch princess with her wonder potion,
no rabbit in the hat or salt,
just wishing my wish would come true once.

Chorus:
Abracadabra, this must work,
Abracadabraz, start loving me.

Verse 2:
Eating bat claws, lizard soup,
reciting spells tonight,
seeing light in the crystal ball,
torturing my body in vain dreams.

Bridge:
Looking through my scout's handbook,
information book for young people,
Kiss the last frog for look of one woman.

Kohtaus 1:
Hei, hyvä keijus heiluttelemassa taikasauvaansa, 
tai noitanprinsessa ihmejuomallaan, 
ei kaninhattua tai suolaa, 
vain toivoen toiveeni toteutuvan kerran.

Kertosäe: 
Abracadabra, tämän pitäisi toimia, 
Abracadabraz, ala rakastamaan minua.

Kohtaus 2:
Syömässä lintujen kynsiä, liskojen keittoa, 
loitsien lukemista tänä iltana, 
valon näkemistä kristallipallosta, 
turhaan pilaamalla unia. 

Sillan:
Katselemaan väijyjäni käsikirjaa, 
nuorisolle tarkoitettua tietokirjaa, 
suudella viimeinen sammakko saadaksesi yhden naisen muodon.

1. What Mila Smith (born 2009, likes KoreaPop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- Wow, this cool! It has a magical vibe to it with all this talk of fairies, witches, and potions. It reminds me of the K-Pop songs I love. I'm not so sure about the idea of wishing for someone to "start loving me," though. That kind of seems a little awkward and desperate.

2. What Paul Lee (born 2003, likes Rap) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- I don't really get the whole fantasy element of this song. It doesn't seem very rap-like to me. Plus, I'm not sure about the whole Abracadabra thing - that sounds a little childish and silly.

3. What Tina Smith (born 1996, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- I really like the retro sound of this song and the almost mystical feel. It's got a classic pop vibe that I'm definitely into. I'm not sure about the mention of the witch, though. That kind of thing isn't really my thing.

4. What Bobby Reynolds (born 1995, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- This isn't really my type of music - it feels a bit too soft and poppy for me. I don't like the witch and wizard references either - it kind of takes away from the rock edge of the song.

5. What Rachel Johnson (born 1992, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- This is a really nice sing-along kind of song - it's got a cheerful tune and easy to remember lyrics. I'm not sure about the fantasy references, though. I can kind of get behind it, but it feels a bit too abstract for me.

6. What Shawn Johnson (born 1991, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- This song is alright, but it's not really my type of music. I'm all about hard rock, not fluffy pop-facts. And this one is a bit too light for my tastes - and the lyrics about a witch and a crystal ball are a bit too cheesy for me.

7. What Jake White (born 1989, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- This is really catchy and it has a magical feel to it. I love the way the lyrics mix fantasy with reality. I'm not sure about the parts where it talks about wishing for someone to "start loving me," though. That seems a bit desperate.

8. What Cyrus McCall (born 1988, likes Rap) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- This is a neat song, but it's not really my style. I don't really get the fantasy stuff. Plus, I'm not sure about the whole Abracadabra thing - that sounds a bit childish and silly.

9. What Kelly Taylor (born 1987, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- I like the energy that this song has, but I'm not sure about the witchy stuff. It kind of takes away from the rock edge of the song. And I'm not sure about the part where it talks about wishing for someone to "start loving me" - that seems kind of desperate.

10. What Mike Richards (born 1977, likes Metal) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
- This song is alright, but it's not really my type of music. I'm all about heavy metal, not fluffy pop fantasy. And this one is a bit too light for my tastes - and the lyrics about a witch and a crystal ball are a bit too cheesy for me.

Scene 1:
Hey there, good fairy waving her wand, 
Or princess with her magical brew, 
No rabbit's hat or pinch of salt, 
Just hoping my wish will come true one day.

Chorus: 
Abracadabra, this should do me some good, 
Abracadabraz, start loving me like it should.

Scene 2:
Eating birds' claws, lizards' stew, 
Reading spells this evening too, 
Seeing light from the crystal ball, 
Dreams ruined, that's no good at all. 

Bridge:
Scrutinizing my own grimoire, 
A book for the youth's lore, 
Kissing the last frog to get one woman's form.

Tippity tap, feeling cool,
Gotta lotta magic tools,
No guile just a big old smile,
Hoping one day things will be alright.

Abracadabra, gonna get through this story,
Abracadabraz, life's gonna get a bit more glory.

Eatin' lizards, watchin' news,
Studyin' spells and singin' the blues,
Gleamin' light off a mystic orb,
Dreams interrupted, ain't doin' so well.

Paging through a great big book,
A cheat code for us to look,
Kissed the toad to get a good look,
One woman's form, yeah, yeah, yeah.
